displayProperties.name: Glacier Grenade
displayProperties.description: A grenade that creates walls out of Stasis crystals to block damage and freeze targets; these walls can be shattered for damage.

displayProperties.name: Cold Calculations
displayProperties.description: In strikes, defeat combatants with [Stasis] Stasis damage and defeat combatants that are frozen by Stasis.

displayProperties.name: Reforged in the Light
displayProperties.description:
Meditating at the statue has infused your new armor with the Light but its connection to the Traveler could be made stronger.

Return to Eva.

displayProperties.name: Trial in the Clouds
displayProperties.description:
Ghost receives coordinates to a literal floating island somewhere off the coast of the Winding Cove in the European Dead Zone. It's been cheekily dubbed "The European Aerial Zone," and apparently it's an excellent place to perform combat drills and meditate.

Investigate the European Aerial Zone.

displayProperties.name: The Holiday Begins
displayProperties.description:
The Solstice of Heroes is a holiday in which Guardians reflect on past battles and celebrate their many efforts to defend humanity. Eva Levante has returned to help usher in the festivities.

Speak to Eva Levante in the Tower.

displayProperties.name: Breathe In, Breathe Out
displayProperties.description: Eva suggests you meditate on the meaning of the Solstice and the nature of renewal at the Statue of Heroes in the Tower Courtyard.

displayProperties.name: But Wait, There's More!
displayProperties.description:
As you finish your exploration of the Aerial Zone, Ghost receives a message from Eva herself. She'd like to speak to you at your earliest convenience.

Visit Eva Levante in the Tower.

displayProperties.name: Seasonal
displayProperties.description: Quests related to Seasons.

displayProperties.name: Solstice Packages: Superior Tier II

displayProperties.name: Gilded Conquest
displayProperties.description: Use Cabal Gold to socket a Challenger Medallion into the Hammer of Proving. Once done, you will be ready to issue a challenge. The Hammer of Proving can be found in the Quest tab of the Director.

displayProperties.name: Precious Plunder
displayProperties.description:
Wield the Hammer of Proving to pillage Cabal Gold by completing playlist strikes, Gambit, Crucible, public events, dungeons, Nightmare Hunts, or the Blind Well.

The Hammer of Proving permits challenges of honorable combat to be issued, skirting the risk of total war with the Cabal. However, to be recognized as legitimate, it must be socketed with Cabal Gold.

displayProperties.description: Speak with Zavala in the Tower Courtyard.

The Battlegrounds playlist may be found in the Director under Vanguard missions.
